===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|かた}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=かた|-}}, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|*kata-|sort=かた}}. First cited in the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' of 720.<ref name="KDJ2">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2}}</ref>

Japanese sources describe this as cognate with {{ja-r|方|かた|side, direction}}.<ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref> However, the pitch accents differ: compounds starting with {{m|ja|片}} show <code><LL-></code> accent in the {{w|Heian period}}, in contrast to {{m|ja|方}}, which is recorded with a <code><HL></code> accent instead, suggesting no direct relationship between the two. 

Alternatively, {{ja-r|肩|かた|t=shoulder}} might be a more likely cognate given that term's matching <code><LH></code> accent and compounds also indicating homonymy: compare {{ja-r|傾げる|かたげる|t=to tilt, to incline}}, {{ja-r|担げる|かたげる|t=to carry on one’s shoulder}}. Also, accent comparison might support that this word derives from the verb root {{ja-r|勝つ|かつ|to win; to tend to}} or {{ja-r|搗つ|かつ|to pound}} (both have an <code><L-></code> accent), and adverb {{ja-r|且つ|かつ|besides; moreover; also; and}} which has an <code><LF></code> accent.

